Thank you to all my super hero friends for helping turn my visions into reality.

These are my incredibly honest/vulnerable thoughts on me making music in Spanish and specifically to the Latino/Latina/Spanish community. I would love feedback and constructive criticism on the matter. This entire process has been so terrifying for the fact that I have no idea what I’m doing, I DONT SING, i am NOT Latina  or Spanish and I AM LEARNING Spanish but I have taken it one step at a time over the years and it has flowed and been such a expanding/growing/learning experience for me. Even when I mentally and physically want to quit, I end up going back to it. So… I would love to proceed with the most considerate and conscious actions moving forward being as, I’ve created what I’ve created and at this point I have two options: to hide it out of fear of culture-vulturing/ being misunderstood or …sharing it. Making songs about things has been an expression of mine since I was little, I do it to remember and learn. I’ve done it about science, vocabulary, bio, chemistry, throughout school ect. With two learning disabilities it has always been a fun and useful way to get things to stick in my head. That’s one of the main reasons I began doing this, that and I absolutely love it. 
 I welcome you to share your thoughts and advice to help me navigate this.

1/2 of some of my favorite photos from rafting down the Grand Canyon for 13 days this past month. The experience was like nothing I’ve ever done and the views were like nothing I had ever seen. The Canyon is absolutely breathtaking at every turn and the second you think you’ve got her figured out she humbles you with a massive rapid and ragging water. The crew, the food, the stars, the emotional exploration behind going 220 miles down the Colorado river without service, showers, mirrors or a way to get out, turned out to be a fast track to honing into my authentic self, this trip felt like I was ten years old again just playing and exploring for thirteen days straight. If you ever get the chance to do this trip I couldn’t recommend it enough.
